06:28.756 --> 06:30.889
caring about a lot
of things right now.

06:31.657 --> 06:33.959
Are you talking to anyone?

06:34.961 --> 06:36.194
Hmm.

06:37.230 --> 06:38.597
"Anyone"?

06:39.432 --> 06:41.032
Are you?

06:42.502 --> 06:43.802
Just 'cause people
are the people

06:43.804 --> 06:45.036
you're supposed to talk to,

06:45.038 --> 06:46.571
it doesn't mean you
can talk to them.

07:02.121 --> 07:04.022
<i>So, just a few things
before you go.</i>

07:04.024 --> 07:07.793
I'm sure your kids are all caught
up in their class work, yes?

07:07.795 --> 07:09.361
Uh, why?

07:09.363 --> 07:11.163
They can't go on the trip if
they're missing assignments.

07:11.165 --> 07:12.097
School policy.

07:12.099 --> 07:13.932
I already spoke to
the other teachers.

07:13.934 --> 07:15.066
And so I'm just checking...

07:15.068 --> 07:16.768
Oh, yes. No. Of course.
Yeah, of course.

07:16.770 --> 07:19.237
Okay. Good, good.

07:19.239 --> 07:21.473
Our main concern is, uh,

07:21.475 --> 07:22.874
William Mitman.

07:22.876 --> 07:24.676
- Billy?
- Yeah, Billy.

07:24.678 --> 07:27.078
I don't know if you're
aware of his issues.

07:27.080 --> 07:30.015
But we wouldn't
be letting him go

07:30.017 --> 07:31.416
unless he was 100%.

07:31.418 --> 07:32.951
But Legal just
wants to make sure

07:32.953 --> 07:37.022
that I discuss this with you,
just to keep your eyes open.

07:37.024 --> 07:39.891
What he has is a
behavioral disorder.

07:39.893 --> 07:42.861
And he will be taking his
medication with him on the trip.

07:42.863 --> 07:47.232
He's allowed to administer
the medication himself.

07:47.234 --> 07:51.002
Between you and me, I
think there's just

07:51.471 --> 07:53.805
some tension at home,

07:53.807 --> 07:55.974
so they just wanna show
him a little trust

07:55.976 --> 07:57.742
by letting him go on this trip.

07:57.744 --> 08:01.847
But you have my number,
so if you need me, call.

08:38.217 --> 08:39.618
- Hey, Sam.
- Hey!

08:39.620 --> 08:41.820
Sweet ride, Miss S.

08:50.396 --> 08:51.463
Hi.

08:52.198 --> 08:53.765
I brought the test.

08:53.767 --> 08:56.167
You're taking it this weekend.
No excuses.

08:56.569 --> 08:57.869
Uh, what test?

08:57.871 --> 08:59.271
Take care of yourself, Margot.

08:59.273 --> 09:01.373
Oh, the <i>Gatsby</i> test? Why
didn't Billy take...

09:01.375 --> 09:04.075
- Margot.
- Sorry.

09:04.077 --> 09:05.343
Okay.

09:06.713 --> 09:08.346
Are you ready?

09:21.360 --> 09:25.497
♪

09:35.241 --> 09:36.808
What's that light?

09:37.810 --> 09:39.744
That? That thing's
been on forever.

09:39.746 --> 09:41.246
Wait, your warning light is on?

09:41.248 --> 09:42.614
It's nothing.

09:42.616 --> 09:45.684
Well, if it were nothing
it wouldn't be on.

09:45.686 --> 09:48.587
It's a really old
car, it kind of just

09:48.589 --> 09:49.854
does things sometimes.

09:49.856 --> 09:51.122
It just does things sometimes?

09:51.124 --> 09:52.691
Do you want us to
stop and deal with it

09:52.693 --> 09:54.492
even though we're
already running late?

10:00.166 --> 10:01.700
Well, on behalf of all of us,

10:01.702 --> 10:03.902
I would just like to say
how grateful we are

10:03.904 --> 10:05.670
that you're taking us
to the competition.

10:05.672 --> 10:08.773
I mean, since the school
cut our arts program,

10:08.775 --> 10:11.576
it's important to get
exposure wherever we can.

10:11.578 --> 10:13.812
Yeah, seriously.

10:15.982 --> 10:17.816
Don't you think it's
interesting, Miss Stevens,

10:17.818 --> 10:20.752
that we spend almost
every day together

10:20.754 --> 10:22.921
and we talk about so
many different things,

10:22.923 --> 10:26.057
but we don't really
know each other?

10:26.759 --> 10:29.260
I mean, not really.

11:00.493 --> 11:02.327
I wanna talk to you about life.

11:02.329 --> 11:05.530
It's just too difficult
to be alive, isn't it?

11:05.532 --> 11:06.898
And to try to function.

11:06.900 --> 11:08.900
There are all these
people to deal with.

11:08.902 --> 11:11.136
Like, when I was at
the supermarket,

11:11.138 --> 11:13.405
trying to buy a
can of tuna fish,

11:13.407 --> 11:15.907
and there was someone
standing right in front

11:15.909 --> 11:18.777
who wanted to reach out
and grab the tuna fish.

11:18.779 --> 11:21.780
And I waited a while
to see if they'd move,

11:21.782 --> 11:22.947
but they didn't.

11:22.949 --> 11:24.749
They were looking at
the tun fish, too,

11:24.751 --> 11:26.317
but they were taking
a really long time,

11:26.319 --> 11:28.620
and they're reading each
ingredient like they were...

11:30.424 --> 11:31.656
What was that?

11:31.658 --> 11:33.191
Shit.

11:33.193 --> 11:34.659
Oh, shit. Sorry.

11:34.661 --> 11:36.061
No, seriously. What was that?

11:36.063 --> 11:37.696
- I think it was the tire.
- Oh, my God!

11:37.698 --> 11:39.130
Fuck! Sorry. Shit.

11:39.132 --> 11:40.632
- Oh, my God!
- Sorry, sorry.

11:48.541 --> 11:50.008
Sam.

11:50.010 --> 11:52.877
Sam, your monologue was really
good so far, I'm sorry.

11:52.879 --> 11:54.245
It's Christopher Durang, right?

11:54.247 --> 11:55.814
I didn't think you knew
who Christopher...

11:55.816 --> 11:58.183
Guys! We're sitting on
the side of the road.

11:58.185 --> 11:59.050
Right.

11:59.052 --> 12:00.285
It was the warning
light, wasn't it?

12:00.287 --> 12:02.187
It wasn't the warning
light, Margot.

12:02.189 --> 12:02.921
Oh, Jesus!

12:02.923 --> 12:03.988
You guys, please.

12:03.990 --> 12:05.490
Guys, please, please.
Come on, stop.

12:05.492 --> 12:08.760
You are driving other people's
children in an unfit automobile.

12:08.762 --> 12:10.929
I'm sorry. I'm
really embarrassed.

12:10.931 --> 12:12.397
Why are you embarrassed?

12:12.399 --> 12:13.732
Because I am the asshole

12:13.734 --> 12:16.668
who ignores a big,
flashing orange light.

12:16.670 --> 12:18.269
You curse a lot.

12:18.271 --> 12:20.472
- I know.
- When we're at school...

12:20.474 --> 12:21.673
It's just a switch.

12:21.675 --> 12:23.141
Why isn't the switch on now?

12:23.143 --> 12:25.477
Because we're not at school.

12:26.278 --> 12:28.546
But, like, we are.

12:32.318 --> 12:33.952
Right.

12:34.153 --> 12:35.286
Okay.

13:01.914 --> 13:04.249
We're gonna be so late.

13:04.251 --> 13:07.418
I have to call the hotel.
I'm gonna call the hotel.

13:13.559 --> 13:16.060
Hi. This is Margot Jensen
from Franklin High School.

13:16.062 --> 13:17.595
Is this the front desk?

13:22.434 --> 13:23.768
Where do I...

13:23.770 --> 13:25.270
Where it says "signature".

13:25.272 --> 13:26.938
Oh.

13:26.940 --> 13:28.940
Make sure you get that
to your service station

13:28.942 --> 13:30.608
as soon as you possibly can.

13:30.610 --> 13:32.544
Drive too long on the spare...

13:32.546 --> 13:34.145
Right. Okay. Will do.

13:34.147 --> 13:36.381
- Thank you.
- Great. Thank you.

13:36.383 --> 13:37.982
Thank you.

13:54.600 --> 13:57.235
♪

14:00.339 --> 14:03.408
All of your music is... old.

14:03.410 --> 14:04.976
Oh, I'm sorry.

14:04.978 --> 14:07.345
- I'll change the station.
- No!

14:07.347 --> 14:09.080
I love this song.

14:10.549 --> 14:11.950
How do you know this song?

14:11.952 --> 14:13.785
- My dad...
- Exactly.

14:13.787 --> 14:16.588
This is dad music.

14:16.590 --> 14:17.889
Yeah.

14:17.891 --> 14:19.891
And old lady teacher music.

14:19.893 --> 14:21.559
You are not old.

14:21.561 --> 14:23.895
No, I am old.

14:23.897 --> 14:25.430
You like America?

14:25.432 --> 14:26.998
- Well...
- America?

14:27.000 --> 14:28.666
The band. This band.

14:28.668 --> 14:29.968
America.

14:29.970 --> 14:31.169
It's just called "America"?

14:31.171 --> 14:32.731
- Yep.
- And that's it?

14:33.639 --> 14:35.740
That's it.

14:36.842 --> 14:38.142
I don't know, Margot.

14:38.144 --> 14:40.378
I kinda like what
it's doing to me.

14:41.447 --> 14:43.715
Do you mind if I ask
how old you are?

14:43.717 --> 14:46.117
Sam thinks you're 26, but
I think you're older.

14:46.119 --> 14:47.352
Not 'cause you look older,

14:47.354 --> 14:48.820
you just seem older.
My older sister...

14:48.822 --> 14:50.722
Twenty-nine.

14:50.724 --> 14:52.290
Best part.

14:52.292 --> 14:54.092
<i>♪ Will you meet me</i>

14:54.094 --> 14:55.727
<i>♪ In the middle</i>

14:55.729 --> 14:57.629
<i>♪ Will you meet me</i>

14:57.631 --> 14:59.264
<i>♪ In the air?</i>

14:59.266 --> 15:01.032
<i>♪ Will you love me</i>

15:01.034 --> 15:02.433
<i>♪ Just a little</i>

15:02.435 --> 15:06.404
<i>♪ Just enough To show you care? ♪</i>

15:06.406 --> 15:08.506
<i>♪ Well, I tried to fake it</i>

15:08.508 --> 15:12.710
<i>♪ I don't mind sayin' I
just can't make it ♪</i>

15:19.285 --> 15:21.586
♪

15:31.630 --> 15:35.199
<i>♪ Well, I keep on
Thinkin' 'bout you ♪</i>

15:35.201 --> 15:38.836
♪ Sister Golden Hair surprise

15:38.838 --> 15:40.638
<i>♪ And I just can't</i>

15:40.640 --> 15:41.773
<i>♪ Live without you</i>

15:41.775 --> 15:45.710
<i>♪ Can't you see it In my eyes... ♪</i>

15:58.657 --> 16:00.491
I'm gonna go check us in.

16:25.217 --> 16:28.052
- Another glass?
- Oh. Um...

16:28.054 --> 16:29.420
Sure. Thank you.

16:29.422 --> 16:32.457
Another vino for the
lady, coming right up.

16:32.459 --> 16:34.425
So, what was your favorite part?

16:35.094 --> 16:37.228
Oh, gosh. Um...

16:37.230 --> 16:39.530
We did <i>The Glass Menagerie.</i>

16:40.632 --> 16:41.933
I loved that play.

16:41.935 --> 16:43.167
And who were you?

16:43.169 --> 16:44.435
I was Tom.

16:44.437 --> 16:46.404
I ended up playing boys a lot.

16:46.406 --> 16:47.405
Why?

16:47.407 --> 16:50.441
I don't know. I... I was tall.

16:50.443 --> 16:51.976
I don't really have hips.

16:51.978 --> 16:53.911
- Here you go.
- Thank you.

16:55.481 --> 16:57.281
<i>Pinot noir.</i>

16:57.283 --> 16:58.950
Such a good choice.

17:00.352 --> 17:01.919
Totally.

17:01.921 --> 17:03.988
It is.

17:03.990 --> 17:05.289
So are we excited to see

17:05.290 --> 17:06.357
who's gonna be there tonight?

17:06.358 --> 17:08.358
- Pretty interesting...
- Oh.

17:08.361 --> 17:12.130
Man. There was this...
There was this one time...

17:12.132 --> 17:14.365
What?

17:14.367 --> 17:16.367
Gosh, I haven't thought
about this in years.

17:16.368 --> 17:20.070
We were doing <i>Taming
of the Shrew.</i>

17:20.073 --> 17:22.040
And I played Petruchio.

17:22.041 --> 17:24.909
And in the last scene,
on the last night...

17:24.911 --> 17:26.676
Petruchio is the main character.

17:26.679 --> 17:27.878
Right. Sorry. But...

17:27.881 --> 17:30.014
Petruchio is this guy who's
in love with this girl...

17:30.016 --> 17:31.215
Kate.

17:31.217 --> 17:33.017
And in the last scene,
the girl playing Kate,

17:33.019 --> 17:35.853
this girl... Gillian.

17:35.855 --> 17:38.890
She... kisses me.

17:38.892 --> 17:42.627
We'd been doing it with this...
This stupid hug.

17:42.629 --> 17:44.295
Because it was that
kind of school.

17:44.297 --> 17:48.666
So I go in for the stupid
hug, and she just...

17:48.668 --> 17:50.701
turns her head and...

17:52.004 --> 17:53.604
And kisses me.

17:55.174 --> 17:56.741
Really kisses me.

17:57.810 --> 17:59.944
And I remember

17:59.946 --> 18:03.548
thinking why didn't we do
this in the first place?

18:03.550 --> 18:05.750
These two people are in love.

18:05.752 --> 18:09.120
And then it hit me
that my teachers,

18:09.122 --> 18:11.055
my mother,

18:11.057 --> 18:13.458
my grandmother and...

18:13.460 --> 18:16.794
And the boy I liked, Thomas...

18:16.796 --> 18:21.399
O'Toole, are all out
there watching me

18:21.401 --> 18:23.968
make out with Gillian Cooke.

18:23.970 --> 18:25.703
God! That's crazy.

18:25.705 --> 18:26.704
What happened?

18:26.706 --> 18:29.574
We had to go to the
principal's office.

18:29.576 --> 18:32.510
But didn't you tell
them it was her fault?

18:34.046 --> 18:35.446
No.

18:36.448 --> 18:37.715
Why not?

18:38.183 --> 18:40.384
I don't know.

18:40.386 --> 18:42.720
It didn't feel like
it was her fault.

18:43.989 --> 18:45.256
I totally get it.

18:45.258 --> 18:48.392
And if we... One of us
had actually been a boy,

18:48.394 --> 18:51.395
we wouldn't have got into...
trouble at all.

18:51.397 --> 18:52.730
They wouldn't have cared.

18:52.732 --> 18:54.772
They would have clapped and
thought you were dating.

18:55.367 --> 18:57.268
I never did another play.

18:57.270 --> 18:59.537
Still good on that wine?

18:59.539 --> 19:01.239
Are you trying to get me drunk?

19:04.109 --> 19:07.578
Yeah. No, I'm good. Thank you.

19:07.580 --> 19:10.148
- No more for...
- Can you...

19:10.150 --> 19:11.449
Margot.

19:11.451 --> 19:13.885
Well, we should get going.
We're gonna be late.

19:14.786 --> 19:16.387
Again.

19:19.458 --> 19:22.493
Most of you will be eliminated.

19:22.495 --> 19:24.729
And it will be difficult.

19:24.731 --> 19:28.366
So much of acting is
about the struggle.

19:28.368 --> 19:29.967
But some of you,

19:29.969 --> 19:32.470
the truly talented few,

19:32.472 --> 19:35.273
will earn the right to
stand on this stage

19:35.275 --> 19:36.841
and be heard by all.

19:36.843 --> 19:39.977
And an even smaller group
will experience...

19:40.946 --> 19:42.547
the exhilaration...

19:44.149 --> 19:45.716
of the win.

19:46.385 --> 19:47.985
On Sunday afternoon,

19:47.987 --> 19:50.521
three winners will be chosen

19:50.523 --> 19:53.191
by our esteemed panel of judges.

19:53.193 --> 19:55.660
Give them a round of applause.

19:57.197 --> 19:58.996
He's a big guy.

19:58.998 --> 20:00.198
The director.

20:00.200 --> 20:01.599
He also directs this teen soap.

20:01.601 --> 20:03.901
Every year we begin with
a group affirmation.

20:03.903 --> 20:04.902
